<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="CH1c0892-en-e68c5d6f" type="transl"><teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Glory of Yue</title><editor role="translator">Olivia Milburn</editor></titleStmt><publicationStmt><ab>published electronically as part of the TLS project at https://hxwd.org</ab><availability status="4">The copyright status of this work is unclear</availability></publicationStmt><sourceDesc><bibl><title>The Glory of Yue</title>Leiden: Brill, 2010</bibl><ab>Translation of <bibl corresp="#CH1c0892"><title xml:lang="och">越絕書</title></bibl> into <lang xml:lang="en">English</lang>.</ab></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><creation resp="#CH">Initially created: <date>2023-11-28T06:14:15.313+09:00</date> by CH</creation><creation resp="#CH">Header modified: <date>2023-11-28T06:16:04.056+09:00</date> by CH</creation></profileDesc></teiHeader><text><body><div><head>Translated parts</head><p xml:id="CH1c0892-start"><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-1a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:17:50.325+09:00">!e question is put:</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-1a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:18:03.957+09:00">“What is meant by Yuejue 越絕?”</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-1a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:18:17.259+09:00">[We say:] Yue is thename of a country.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-1a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:18:33.148+09:00">The question is put:] “Why is it called that?”</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-1a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:19:02.847+09:00">[We say:] According tothe records of Qi and Lu found in the Chunqiu 春秋(Spring and AutumnAnnals),</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-1a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:19:43.769+09:00">these are the names of countries which can also be used as surnames,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-1a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:19:52.485+09:00">this is quite clear.5</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-1a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:20:18.926+09:00">Jue means ‘account.’6</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-1a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:20:40.47+09:00">It is a reference to thetime of [King] Goujian [of Yue].</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-1a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:20:49.53+09:00">At that time,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-1a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:21:01.32+09:00">Qi was about to attack Lu,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-1a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:21:13.392+09:00">and Confucius thought this to be a shameful act,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-1a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:21:33.28+09:00">and so Zigong went topersuade Qi to leave Lu in peace.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-1a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:22:42.493+09:00">In one fell swoop Zigong</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-1a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:22:49.149+09:00">brought civilwar to Qi,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-1a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:22:58.894+09:00">destroyed Wu,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-1a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:23:08.302+09:00">advanced Jin,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-1a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:23:14.249+09:00">and strengthened Yue.7</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-1a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:23:29.691+09:00">Later onan exceptional scholar noticed</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-1a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:23:39.433+09:00">that when Confucius wrote the Chunqiu春秋(Spring andAutumnAnnals),</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-1a.22" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:24:58.679+09:00"> This exceptional scholar] also realised that Zigong and the Sage were not so far apart in ability,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-1a.23" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:25:32.606+09:00">[indeed they were in the same relationship]as the lips and the teeth,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-1a.24" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:25:50.2+09:00">the coat and the lining.9</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-1a.25" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:26:10.168+09:00">Therefore he selectedcrucial events,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-1a.26" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:26:33.107+09:00">and wrote a historical record that would record thesematters.10</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-2a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:27:02.921+09:00">The question is put:</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-2a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:27:16.716+09:00">“Why not call this book the Canonical Recordsof Yue?</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-2a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:27:32.332+09:00">Why use the term jue?”11</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-2a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:28:07.31+09:00">We say:</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-2a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:28:36.189+09:00">Juealso means ‘glory.’12</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-2a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:28:28.937+09:00">"That would be wrong.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-2a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:28:51.048+09:00">In the time of [King] Goujian [of Yue],</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-2a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:29:02.095+09:00">the Son ofHeaven was weak and feeble,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-2a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:29:08.609+09:00">and the feudal lords all rebelled againsthis authority.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-2a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:29:16.037+09:00">At this point Goujian held back the strong and supportedthe weak;</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-2a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:29:31.076+09:00">he stopped evil and turned it into good.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-2a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:29:46.135+09:00">The Way determinedhis choices,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-2a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:30:13.663+09:00">and so he returned the lands of Pei 沛 to Song,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-2a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:30:19.618+09:00">restoredFuling 浮陵 to Chu,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-2a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:30:56.154+09:00">and handed back Linyi 臨沂 and Kaiyang 開陽</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-2a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:31:03.151+09:00">toLu.13 </seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-2a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:32:04.886+09:00">He put a stop to wars and invasions</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-2a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:32:14.937+09:00">among the states of the Zhou confederacy.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-2a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:32:23.461+09:00">In governing his own state he was sincere and trustworthy,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-2a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:32:37.834+09:00">in diplomacy he made use of his might and authority.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-2a.22" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:32:52.801+09:00">[The king of] Yuewas uniquely successful;</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-2a.23" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:36:42.684+09:00"> therefore this book is called the Yuejue (TheAccount of Yue/The Glory of Yue).14</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-2a.24" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:33:28.753+09:00">The authors of this [book]</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-2a.25" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:33:43.393+09:00"> respectedthe fact that on the one hand he was highly self-controlled,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-2a.26" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:34:04.698+09:00">and on theother he was the greatest [monarch of the age].</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-2a.27" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:34:51.072+09:00"> !e texts left by clevermen</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-2a.28" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:35:00.487+09:00">should not be ignored,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1c0892_CHANT_001-2a.29" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-11-28T06:35:07.827+09:00">so it is clear that it would not be suitable tocall this book a record.15</seg></p></div></body></text></TEI>